Trim the @carrot{1} then coarsely grate (no need to peel). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}. Pop half of the beans into a #bowl{} and mash with the back of a #fork{} or #potato masher{}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @cumin seeds{1/2%tsp} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer them into a small bowl and return the pan to the heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. When hot, add the @garlic{} and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add both the crushed and whole black beans to the pan along with the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and a quarter of the @korma curry paste{50%g}. Add the @water{50%ml} for the beans and bring to a simmer. Cook until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in another large frying pan on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{210%g} and remaining korma paste. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and pop into a bowl with the baby gem lettuce. Add the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} and lemon zest, mix well. Pop the carrot and toasted cumin seeds into another bowl. Squeeze in some lemon juice and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. This is your carrot kachumber.

Once everything is ready, reheat the bean mix if needed and share between your @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4}. Top with the chicken and carrot kachumber. Roll up your wraps and serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!